<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="hive.lab"
      xml:lang="en"
      lang="en">
  <metal:content-core fill-slot="content-core">
    <metal:content-core define-macro="content-core">
        <tal:data define="form view/crudform">
            <tal:hasdata tal:condition="form">
                Aliquot that have incorrect data. Please update and return to the checked in state.
                <tal:crud replace="structure form" />
                <a href="#" name="" style="display:none"></a>
                <br class="visualClear" />
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <b>Save Changes</b>: Save changes to all aliquot.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b>Check Back In</b>:Release the hold on the selected aliquot, returning them to a checked in state.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <b><a href="./checkout">Check Out</a></b>: Place the selected aliquot in the final stage for check out. After you have selected all of the aliquot for check out, proceed to the <a href="./checkout">check out screen</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                     <b>Hold</b>: Place a hold on the aliquot. That will hide it in this view, and only make it available if the "Show all" option is selected in the filter above.
                    </li>
            </tal:hasdata>
            <tal:nodata tal:condition="not:form">
                <p>No Aliquot are marked as inaccurate.</p>
            </tal:nodata>
        </tal:data>
    </metal:content-core>
  </metal:content-core>
</html>